To analyze the sentence and produce a dependency tree, we will use the following steps:

1. Tokenize the sentence: Break the sentence into individual tokens. These can be words, punctuation marks, etc.

2. Define the part-of-speech (POS) for each token: This step involves determining the grammatical category (noun, verb, adjective, etc.) for each token.

3. Identify dependencies: Based on the POS tags and the grammatical rules of the language, identify the head token for each dependency. This is the token that is central to the relationship.

